-- Best Buy Third-Quarter Profit Trails Projections; Company Cuts Forecast
-- B y   S t e v e n   F r o m m
-- 2010-12-14T13:04:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-14/best-buy-third-quarter-profit-trails-projections-company-cuts-forecast.html
(Corrects yesterday's closing stock price.)  Best Buy Co. reported a third-
quarter profit of 54 cents a share, missing analyst 
estimates and sending the retailer's shares lower.  The average estimate of analysts surveyed by Bloomberg was
for a profit of 60 cents a share.  Best Buy said it expects annual earnings of $3.20 to 
$3.40 a share, less than its forecast of $3.55 to $3.70.
The average estimate of analysts surveyed by Bloomberg was for 
a profit of $3.59 a share.  The retailer's stock fell as low as $37.16 from its close
yesterday of $41.70. Best Buy is based in Richfield, Minnesota.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steven Fromm at 
 sfromm@bloomberg.net  